Class menu

  • java.lang.Object
    • phoenix.menu

  • public final class menu
extends java.lang.Object
    API Generated: Tue May 17 06:47:42 EDT 2016
    API Source: DynamicMenusAPI
    STV api calls related to Dynamic Menus.

    NOTE: Many Dynamic Menu fields return a DynamicVariable. A DynamicVariable is like a regular field but it can dynamically store a property reference, sage expression, or a static value.

    For display purposes, any calls that return a DynamicVariable should display fine in the STV.

    BUT, if you need to do logic on a DynamicValue (ie, boolean or int), then you should use the GetComputedValue(DynamicValue) which will return the computed value as a type, ie, boolean, int, etc.

    If you need to change the value of a DynamicVariable then you should use the SetStoredValue method which enabled you to change the value of the variable. Using this method you can change the property, expression or static value of a DynamicVariable.

        public static boolean SaveFragment(IMenuItem item,
                                   java.lang.String parentMenuId,
                                   java.lang.String insertBefore,
                                   java.lang.String insertAfter)
        Saves the given IMenuItem (which can be a Menu or MenuItem since the both implement IMenuItem to the userdata menus areas. The filename will be combination of the parent menu, and the item ids combined.
        Parameters:
        item -
        parentMenuId - id of the menu in which to insert this new item (cannot be null)
        insertBefore - id of the element to insert before (can be null)
        insertAfter - id of the elements to insert after (can be null)
        Returns:
        true if the menu fragment was saved
